The Earth impling is an impling that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame, and are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. The player needs at least 36 Hunter to capture this type of impling. Capturing an earth impling grants 25 Hunter experience if caught in Puro-Puro.

With a hunter level of 46 players can catch them barehanded.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening an earth impling jar gives 1,310 worth of loot, on average. This means opening earth impling jars marks an average profit of −440 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −43,979 to get a medium clue scroll from earth impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.
